## Stage 1: Landing Page (Awareness)

### User Actions
- Types URL or clicks bookmark
- Scans landing page for value proposition
- Clicks "Sign In" or "Get Started"

### Touchpoints
- **Page:** Landing page
- **Elements:** Hero section, feature highlights, login button

### Thoughts & Emotions
- üòê **Neutral** - "Let me check the dashboard before my meeting"
- ü§î **Slightly curious** - "Looks professional, hopefully this is faster than the old system"

### Pain Points
- If landing page is slow to load, may refresh or abandon
- If login button is hard to find, causes friction

### Opportunities
- Clear, prominent "Sign In" button
- Quick load time (<1s)
- Trust indicators (security badges, testimonials if relevant)

---

## Stage 2: Authentication (Entry)

### User Actions
- Enters email and password
- Clicks "Sign In"
- (Optional) Uses SSO/OAuth if available

### Touchpoints
- **Page:** Login page
- **Elements:** Email field, password field, "Remember me" checkbox, "Forgot password" link

### Thoughts & Emotions
- üòå **Relieved** - "Good, I remember my password"
- üòü **Anxious** (if error) - "Did I mistype? Is the system down?"

### Pain Points
- Unclear error messages ("Invalid credentials" vs "Email not found")
- No SSO option forces manual login every time
- Forgot password flow is cumbersome

### Opportunities
- Implement SSO for seamless login
- Clear, actionable error messages
- "Remember me" feature for convenience
- Loading state during authentication

---

## Stage 3: Dashboard Home (Initial Impression)

### User Actions
- Scans page for critical alerts (red flags)
- Reads top-level KPIs (bed availability, wait times, revenue)
- Checks timestamp of last data refresh

### Touchpoints
- **Page:** Main dashboard
- **Elements:** KPI cards, charts, department summary, notification bell

### Thoughts & Emotions
- üòä **Satisfied** - "Perfect, everything I need is right here"
- üòÆ **Surprised** (positive) - "Wow, this is much cleaner than the old system"
- üö® **Alarmed** (if critical alert) - "ED wait time is 2x normal, need to investigate"

### Pain Points
- Information overload if too many metrics shown at once
- Unclear what data is real-time vs. cached
- No indication of what requires immediate attention

### Opportunities
- Hierarchy of information (most critical at top)
- Visual indicators for alerts (color coding, icons)
- "Last updated" timestamp for transparency
- Skeleton loaders for data fetching

---

## Stage 4: Explore Metrics (Deep Dive)

### User Actions
- Clicks on specific KPI card (e.g., "ED Wait Times")
- Changes date range to "Last 7 Days"
- Filters by department or shift
- Hovers over chart to see exact values

### Touchpoints
- **Page:** Department detail view or expanded chart modal
- **Elements:** Interactive charts, filters, drill-down buttons

### Thoughts & Emotions
- ü§ì **Engaged** - "Interesting, wait times spiked on Saturday night"
- üí° **Insightful** - "This pattern suggests we need more staff on weekends"
- üò§ **Frustrated** (if slow) - "Why is this taking so long to load?"

### Pain Points
- Slow chart rendering on large datasets
- Cannot compare multiple metrics side-by-side
- Unclear which filters apply to which views

### Opportunities
- Fast, responsive charts with debouncing
- Multi-metric comparison view
- Breadcrumb navigation to show current context
- Persistent filters with visual indication

---

## Stage 5: Generate Report (Export)

### User Actions
- Clicks "Export" or "Download Report"
- Selects format (PDF or CSV)
- Chooses date range and metrics to include
- Downloads file

### Touchpoints
- **Page:** Export modal or dropdown
- **Elements:** Format selector, date picker, metric checkboxes, "Download" button

### Thoughts & Emotions
- ‚úÖ **Accomplished** - "Got what I needed, ready for the meeting"
- üòä **Confident** - "This data will help me make my case to the board"

### Pain Points
- Export takes too long (>10 seconds)
- Downloaded file is poorly formatted or missing data
- Cannot customize report template

### Opportunities
- Background export with progress indicator
- Preview before download
- Save export presets for recurring reports
- Auto-email reports on schedule

---

## Stage 6: Exit/Continue Work

### User Actions
- Logs out or closes browser
- (Or) Navigates to another section of dashboard
- Sets up alerts for future monitoring

### Touchpoints
- **Page:** Any page (logout from navbar)
- **Elements:** Logout button, navigation menu

### Thoughts & Emotions
- üòå **Satisfied** - "This was quick and painless"
- üéØ **Prepared** - "I'm ready for the leadership meeting"

### Pain Points
- No way to save current view for later
- Cannot set up recurring alerts

### Opportunities
- Saved views/bookmarks
- Alert configuration (email/SMS when metric exceeds threshold)
- Quick navigation to return to specific analysis

